Originally submitted by **tomas.jezo** as **issue 15**:

Hey!

First of all thanks for this module! I am constantly running multiple calculations in python and when one hangs up I never know which one from the long list of python instances to kill.

I have tried your module (v1.1.2) and my chosen process title is correctly displayed in ps but not it top (in top it's always python).

I am running the script in python 2.7.1 on Scientific Linux SL release 4.6 (Beryllium) (/etc/redhat-release) 
uname -a returns &quot;Linux lpsc-32-1.in2p3.fr 2.6.9-89.0.16.ELsmp #1 SMP Tue Nov 3 23:35:16 CST 2009 i686 i686 i386 GNU/Linux&quot;
top --version returns &quot;top: procps version 3.2.3&quot;
ps --version returns &quot;procps version 3.2.3&quot;

Thanks!
T.
